<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="light">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="AXIOM01 v3 - The Semantic Rebellion: The Mathematics of Design">
  
  <title>AXIOM01 v3 - The Semantic Rebellion</title>
  
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/axiom.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div id="root">
    <header>
      <nav>
        <a href="#">[Ax<strong>01</strong>]</a>
        <ul>
          <li><button data-nav="hero" aria-current="page">Home</button></li>
          <li><button data-nav="docs">Components</button></li>
          <li><button data-nav="book">Book</button></li>
        </ul>
        <div>
          <button id="theme-toggle" aria-label="Toggle dark mode">🌙</button>
          <button id="menu-toggle" aria-label="Toggle mobile menu" aria-expanded="false">☰</button>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <!-- Mobile menu drawer -->
      <aside id="mobile-menu" class="hidden">
        <nav>
          <ul>
            <li><button data-nav="hero">Home</button></li>
            <li><button data-nav="docs">Components</button></li>
            <li><button data-nav="book">Book</button></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
      </aside>
    </header>

    <main>
      <!-- ================================================================
           HERO VIEW - Landing page with philosophy and CTAs
           ================================================================ -->
      <section id="view-hero">
        <article class="hero">
          <h1>The Semantic Rebellion</h1>
          <p>The Mathematics of Design</p>
          <p>Build beautiful, semantic interfaces with pure CSS, HTML, and minimal JavaScript.</p>
          
          <div>
            <button class="primary" data-nav="docs">Explore Components</button>
            <button class="outline" data-nav="book">Read the Book</button>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Philosophy Principles Section -->
        <section class="container">
          <h2>Three Core Principles</h2>
          <p>AXIOM01 v3 is built on three foundational principles that drive every design decision.</p>
          
          <div class="grid">
            <article class="card">
              <h3>Semantic-First</h3>
              <p>Write meaningful HTML where elements describe WHAT they ARE, not what they look like.</p>
              <p><small>Pure semantic structure. One ID per component. Zero BEM classes.</small></p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Mathematical Design</h3>
              <p>OKLCH color space for perceptually uniform colors that automatically adapt to dark mode.</p>
              <p><small>Design tokens. Spacing scales. Predictable systems.</small></p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Framework Responsibility</h3>
              <p>The framework handles CSS. You write semantic HTML. No build tools required.</p>
              <p><small>Zero dependencies. Static hosting. Ship faster.</small></p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Quick Start Section -->
        <section class="container">
          <h2>Quick Start in 3 Steps</h2>
          <p>Getting started with AXIOM01 v3 is simple. No dependencies, no build process, no learning curve.</p>
          
          <div class="grid">
            <article class="card">
              <h3>1. Link the CSS</h3>
              <p>Import the single CSS file containing all design tokens, components, and utilities.</p>
              <code>&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="axiom.css"&gt;</code>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>2. Write Semantic HTML</h3>
              <p>Use semantic elements (button, article, section, nav) and one root class per component.</p>
              <code>&lt;button class="primary"&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;</code>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>3. Use Design Tokens</h3>
              <p>Reference design tokens for colors, spacing, and typography. Everything scales automatically.</p>
              <code>padding: var(--a-space-md);</code>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Why Semantic HTML Section -->
        <section class="container">
          <h2>Why Semantic HTML?</h2>
          <p>The web has been dominated by utility-first CSS and endless class names for too long. Semantic HTML changes everything.</p>
          
          <div class="grid">
            <article class="card">
              <h3>Accessibility First</h3>
              <p>Semantic HTML is inherently accessible. Screen readers understand meaning. Keyboard navigation works naturally.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>SEO Friendly</h3>
              <p>Search engines understand semantic HTML instantly. No extra markup needed. Content ranks higher.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Maintainable</h3>
              <p>Future developers understand the code immediately. No need to decode class hierarchies or BEM patterns.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Performance</h3>
              <p>Less CSS. Fewer classes. Smaller bundle size. Faster rendering. Better scores on Lighthouse.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Flexible</h3>
              <p>Style any element without classes. Change design by updating CSS variables. No breaking changes.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Simple</h3>
              <p>No learning curve. Just HTML and CSS. No framework concepts, no mental models, no abstractions.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Philosophy in Action Section -->
        <section class="container">
          <h2>Philosophy in Action</h2>
          <p>See how AXIOM01 differs from traditional approaches.</p>
          
          <div class="philosophy-comparison">
            <article class="card">
              <h3>The BEM Way</h3>
              <pre><code>&lt;div class="button button--primary button--large"&gt;
  &lt;span class="button__text"&gt;Click&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

.button { }
.button--primary { }
.button--large { }
.button__text { }</code></pre>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>The AXIOM01 Way</h3>
              <pre><code>&lt;button class="primary"&gt;
  Click
&lt;/button&gt;

button { }
.primary { }</code></pre>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Design Mathematics Section -->
        <section class="container">
          <h2>The Mathematics of Design</h2>
          <p>AXIOM01 uses mathematical relationships for colors, spacing, and typography. Everything scales predictably.</p>
          
          <div class="grid">
            <article class="card">
              <h3>Spacing Scale (1.5x)</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>--a-space-xs: 0.25rem</li>
                <li>--a-space-sm: 0.5rem</li>
                <li>--a-space-md: 0.75rem</li>
                <li>--a-space-lg: 1.125rem</li>
                <li>--a-space-xl: 1.688rem</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Typography Scale (1.25x)</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>--a-text-xs: 0.75rem</li>
                <li>--a-text-sm: 0.875rem</li>
                <li>--a-text-base: 1rem</li>
                <li>--a-text-lg: 1.25rem</li>
                <li>--a-text-xl: 1.563rem</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <h3>Color Space (OKLCH)</h3>
              <p>OKLCH provides perceptually uniform colors that scale mathematically across light and dark modes.</p>
              <p>No more broken colors in dark mode. No more manual adjustments. Mathematics handles it.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Get Started Section -->
        <section class="container">
          <h2>Ready to Join the Rebellion?</h2>
          <p>Explore 77 production-ready components or read the complete guide to semantic-first design.</p>
          <div style="display: flex; gap: var(--a-space-md); flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; margin-top: var(--a-space-lg);">
            <button class="primary" data-nav="docs">Browse Components</button>
            <button class="outline" data-nav="book">Read the Guide</button>
          </div>
        </section>
      </section>

      <!-- ================================================================
           DOCS VIEW - Component library with hub layout
           ================================================================ -->
      <section id="view-docs" class="hidden">
        <article class="hub">
          <!-- Hub header -->
          <header class="container">
            <h1>Component Library</h1>
            <p>All 77 AXIOM01 v3 components, organized by category. Pure semantic HTML. Zero BEM classes.</p>
            
            <!-- Search box -->
            <form>
              <input type="text" id="component-search" placeholder="Search components..." aria-label="Search components">
            </form>
          </header>

          <!-- Hub main layout: sidebar + stage + toc -->
          <div class="container">
            <div class="hub-layout">
              <!-- Left sidebar: categories navigation -->
              <aside>
                <nav>
                  <h3>Categories</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li><a href="#" data-category="buttons">Buttons</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-category="cards">Cards</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-category="forms">Forms</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-category="alerts">Alerts</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-category="layouts">Layouts</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-category="misc">Misc</a></li>
                  </ul>
                </nav>
              </aside>

              <!-- Center stage: component display -->
              <main id="component-stage">
                <div class="grid">
                  <article class="card" data-category="buttons">
                    <h3>Button</h3>
                    <p>Interactive button component with primary, secondary, and ghost variants.</p>
                    <footer>
                      <button class="primary" data-component="button-primary">View</button>
                    </footer>
                  </article>

                  <article class="card" data-category="cards">
                    <h3>Card</h3>
                    <p>Flexible container component with responsive layouts and hover effects.</p>
                    <footer>
                      <button class="primary" data-component="card-basic">View</button>
                    </footer>
                  </article>

                  <article class="card" data-category="forms">
                    <h3>Form Input</h3>
                    <p>Text inputs, textareas, and select dropdowns with validation states.</p>
                    <footer>
                      <button class="primary" data-component="input-text">View</button>
                    </footer>
                  </article>

                  <article class="card" data-category="alerts">
                    <h3>Alert</h3>
                    <p>Alert messages with info, success, warning, and error variants.</p>
                    <footer>
                      <button class="primary" data-component="alert-info">View</button>
                    </footer>
                  </article>

                  <article class="card" data-category="layouts">
                    <h3>Grid Layout</h3>
                    <p>Responsive CSS Grid layout with auto-fit and auto-fill capabilities.</p>
                    <footer>
                      <button class="primary" data-component="grid-3col">View</button>
                    </footer>
                  </article>

                  <article class="card" data-category="misc">
                    <h3>Badge</h3>
                    <p>Small label components for tags, labels, and status indicators.</p>
                    <footer>
                      <button class="primary" data-component="badge">View</button>
                    </footer>
                  </article>
                </div>
              </main>

              <!-- Right sidebar: component info/preview -->
              <aside id="component-preview">
                <h3>Component Details</h3>
                <p>Select a component to view details, code examples, and implementation notes.</p>
              </aside>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <!-- ================================================================
           BOOK VIEW - Book reader with chapter navigation
           ================================================================ -->
      <section id="view-book" class="hidden">
        <article class="hub">
          <!-- Book header -->
          <header class="container">
            <h1>The Semantic Rebellion</h1>
            <p>The Mathematics of Design - Complete Guide</p>
          </header>

          <!-- Book main layout: toc + content + meta -->
          <div class="container">
            <div class="hub-layout">
              <!-- Left sidebar: table of contents -->
              <aside id="book-toc">
                <nav>
                  <h3>Contents</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="intro">Introduction</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-1">1. The Philosophy</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-2">2. Semantic HTML</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-3">3. CSS Layers</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-4">4. Design Tokens</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-5">5. Buttons</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-6">6. Cards</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-7">7. Forms</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-8">8. Responsive</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-9">9. Dark Mode</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-10">10. JavaScript</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-11">11. State</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-12">12. Performance</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-13">13. Content</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-14">14. Scaling</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-15">15. Deployment</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-16">16. Cases</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="chapter-17">17. Future</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#" data-chapter="conclusion">Conclusion</a></li>
                  </ul>
                </nav>
              </aside>

              <!-- Center stage: book content -->
              <main id="book-stage">
                <article>
                  <h2>Introduction</h2>
                  <p>Welcome to AXIOM01 v3: The Semantic Rebellion - The Mathematics of Design.</p>
                  <p>This comprehensive guide explores semantic HTML, CSS innovation, and building interfaces that are beautiful, accessible, and fundamentally simple.</p>
                  
                  <h3>What You'll Learn</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>The philosophy behind semantic-first design</li>
                    <li>OKLCH color space and perceptually uniform colors</li>
                    <li>CSS @layer cascade for override-free styling</li>
                    <li>Design tokens and mathematical scaling</li>
                    <li>Forms and validation without JavaScript</li>
                    <li>Responsive layouts with CSS Grid</li>
                    <li>Accessibility as a foundation, not an afterthought</li>
                    <li>Building a complete framework from first principles</li>
                  </ul>

                  <h3>Why Semantic First?</h3>
                  <p>For decades, web development has been dominated by class-based frameworks and BEM naming conventions. AXIOM01 v3 represents a rebellion against this complexity.</p>
                  <p>We believe that HTML should be meaningful, CSS should be simple, and frameworks should enable developers rather than constrain them.</p>

                  <h3>The Three Principles</h3>
                  <ol>
                    <li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Write meaningful markup where elements and class names describe WHAT they ARE, not HOW they look.</li>
                    <li><strong>Mathematical Design:</strong> Use OKLCH color space for perceptually uniform colors that automatically adapt to dark mode.</li>
                    <li><strong>Framework Responsibility:</strong> The framework handles CSS. You write HTML. No build tools required.</li>
                  </ol>
                </article>
              </main>

              <!-- Right sidebar: chapter metadata -->
              <aside id="book-meta">
                <h3>Chapter Info</h3>
                <p id="chapter-meta-desc">Introduction - Getting started with semantic-first design.</p>
                <nav>
                  <button class="outline" id="prev-chapter">← Previous</button>
                  <button class="outline" id="next-chapter">Next →</button>
                </nav>
              </aside>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <p>AXIOM01 v3 - The Semantic Rebellion: The Mathematics of Design</p>
      <p><small>© 2024 Sol Roth Media. MIT License.</small></p>
    </footer>
  </div>

  <script src="./js/axiom-core.js"></script>
  <script src="./js/component-copy.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
